<dl id="n54121m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54121m">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54121m"> 121(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> melody, rhythm, / mood, manner of man (a sheep) <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54121m"><li>FW 57.02f </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n54121m">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n54121m">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54121m">MS BL 47476a-174</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:369 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n54121m">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;I have practised the <mark>melody</mark> but have not yet acquired the <mark>rhythm</mark>.&rsquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &lsquo;I have not caught the <mark>mood</mark>.&rsquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &lsquo;I have not yet ascertained <mark>the kind of men</mark> who composed the music.&rsquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &lsquo;Now I know who he was,&rsquo; cried Master Kung. &lsquo;His complexion was so dark as to be almost black. He was tall and stout and his eyes when he looked into the distance had the calm gaze of a <mark>sheep</mark>.&rsquo; <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 131</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
